The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 SLC undecided on Moodys assistant 

 - Dias, Ratnayeke, Kalpage being talked about 

LOKENDRA PRATAP SAHI

 Tom Moody feels an assistant coach is necessary 

Colombo: The Sri Lanka Cricket (SLC) brass is still debating whether or not to appoint a desi assistant coach to work under Tom Moody. 

Moody, it may be recalled, told The Telegraph on Friday that the appointment is on the cards. In his opinion, an assistant coach is necessary. 

The coachs own appointment is till the 2007 World Cup. 

Weve spoken about an assistant coach, but nothing has been finalised... The position should be clear within a month, a top SLC official pointed out on Saturday. 

According to the official, former coach Roy Dias name is doing the rounds. Others being talked about are one-time quick Rumesh Ratnayeke, who is currently with the Asian Cricket Council, and former allrounder Ruwan Kalpage. 

Incidentally, Ratnayeke is Asias coach for the three ODIs versus Africa later this month. 




